    • Method Detail

      • registerActivityDemandCompletion

        org.w3c.dom.Document registerActivityDemandCompletion(YFSEnvironment env,
                                                      org.w3c.dom.Document inXML)
                                               throws com.yantra.yfs.japi.YFSException,
                                                      java.rmi.RemoteException

        registerActivityDemandCompletion provides ability to register the extent of completion of the demand. It allows to update the satisfied quantity in table and if quantity satisfied so far exceeds/equals the quantity demanded then DemandSatisfied flag gets updated to value YES. For a License Plate (CaseId/PalletId), DemandSatisfied flag is set to value YES. If the demand is for infinite quantity, the demand never gets completed.

        Related Documents
        Input XML Input DTD Error XML Error DTD

        User Exits: None

        Events Raised:
        Raised during the transaction REGISTER_ACTIVITY_DEMAND.

          ON_SUCCESS:
            This event is raised upon successful execution of registerActivityDemandCompletion.
            Data published - WMS_REGISTER_DEMAND_COMPLETE.ON_SUCCESS.xml

        Audits: None

        Pre Conditions:
        Activity demand should exist in the database for the given Node, ForActivityCode, ShipmentKey (or ShipmentNo) and Item/LPN in the input XML.
        Shipment record corresponding to the activity demand should exist in the database.
        WorkOrder record corresponding to the activity demand should exist in the database.
        Activity demand should not already be in satisfied state.

        Post Conditions:
        Updates the satisfied quantity based on the quantity satisifed for the SKU and marks the demand fulfilled as complete for an LPN and SKU (if quantity satisified exceeds or equals demanded quantity).

        Output Template Support: None

        Database Extensibility Support: No

        Configuration Required for Backward Compatibility: No

        Parameters:
        env - Required. Environment handle returned by the createEnvironment API.
        inXML - Required. For more information, see the associated input xml files.

        Returns:
        No Output XML.

        Throws:
        com.yantra.yfs.japi.YFSException - Exception containing error codes in the standard error files.
        java.rmi.RemoteException - Java's default remote exception handler.
